WEBVTT

00:00.004 --> 00:01.609
<i>Previously</i>
<i>on "Devious Maids"...</i>

00:01.738 --> 00:04.585
Are you having fun watching your
book get made into a movie?

00:04.620 --> 00:06.226
It's not what I expected.

00:06.261 --> 00:07.986
Let me introduce you
to the gang.

00:08.021 --> 00:10.489
Hugh Metzger, I'm obsessed
with your films.

00:10.531 --> 00:12.411
The truth is I didn't
want to get your hopes up.

00:12.433 --> 00:13.493
- About what?
- About your movie

00:13.495 --> 00:15.343
- being back in production.
- I thought it was dead.

00:15.345 --> 00:17.035
Now it's not.
Hugh Metzger wants to direct.

00:17.070 --> 00:18.903
We want you to write it.

00:18.939 --> 00:20.672
Oh, you're the reverend?
Hello.

00:20.708 --> 00:23.007
You seem so...
happy serving others.

00:23.043 --> 00:24.810
Would you like to have dinner
with me tomorrow night?

00:24.845 --> 00:26.177
Zoila, this is my mother.

00:26.213 --> 00:28.380
I like her, too.
But not for you.

00:28.415 --> 00:30.248
I have other plans
for you, Kyle.

00:30.283 --> 00:32.150
I find you intriguing.

00:32.185 --> 00:34.052
You only asked me out
to make Evelyn jealous.

00:34.087 --> 00:35.586
It seems we have
a lot in common.

00:36.890 --> 00:38.389
<i>I never should have
broken up with you.</i>

00:38.424 --> 00:40.658
Give me another chance,
and I will make it up to you.

00:40.693 --> 00:42.693
One thing.
Let's not tell my mother.

00:42.729 --> 00:44.028
Deal.

00:44.064 --> 00:45.730
I brought you a latte...
on the house.

00:45.765 --> 00:47.665
That barista's
got a serious crush on you.

00:47.700 --> 00:50.000
And every time I lead him on,
I get a free coffee.

00:50.035 --> 00:51.201
I know you're my mother now.

00:51.237 --> 00:52.403
Nothing's changed.

00:52.438 --> 00:53.871
You don't want to be my mother?

00:53.906 --> 00:55.840
I'm sorry, Danni,
but I can't be that for you.

00:55.875 --> 00:57.196
Ready to go to the airport?

00:57.209 --> 00:58.743
Just telling my mom
I'm coming home.

00:58.778 --> 01:01.278
Who's that?
Fabian, my hairdresser.

01:01.313 --> 01:03.381
You should read this.
I tried to read it.

01:03.416 --> 01:05.081
- I found it kind of boring.
- You know what?

01:05.117 --> 01:07.517
There's a reason
you didn't understand it.

01:07.552 --> 01:09.586
The ideas in that
book are new...

01:09.621 --> 01:10.787
and you're old.

01:10.822 --> 01:12.589
There's this bad man named Ben.

01:12.624 --> 01:13.625
He's involved
with something

01:13.627 --> 01:14.591
- called The Circle.
- Hold on.

01:14.626 --> 01:17.460
Fabian was always trying
to get me to read this.

01:17.496 --> 01:19.096
It sounds like a cult.

01:19.131 --> 01:20.797
We weren't sure you
could be trusted anymore.

01:20.832 --> 01:23.032
W-W-We?
Mother knows about this?

01:23.067 --> 01:25.375
She's very unhappy with you.

01:26.137 --> 01:28.037
And you know how Mother gets.

01:29.007 --> 01:30.473
Mm.

01:30.609 --> 01:32.442
Mm.

01:32.477 --> 01:35.244
These sheets are heaven.

01:35.280 --> 01:39.048
It's nice staying
at your place...

01:39.083 --> 01:40.549
for a change.

01:40.584 --> 01:42.618
Well, don't get used to it.

01:42.653 --> 01:44.620
My mother comes home
from her trip today.

01:46.757 --> 01:48.257
Kyle...

01:50.995 --> 01:53.329
why are we still keeping this
from her?

01:53.364 --> 01:56.732
Because keeping a secret
is sexy.

01:56.767 --> 01:58.400
Don't you think?

01:58.436 --> 02:00.602
I just hate lying to her.

02:00.638 --> 02:02.137
She's my friend,

02:02.172 --> 02:05.607
and I think she'd be
really happy for us.

02:05.643 --> 02:08.509
Yeah, but I don't want
to share you.

02:08.545 --> 02:10.067
Not yet.

02:12.382 --> 02:14.682
<i>Kyle? I'm home.</i>

02:14.717 --> 02:16.418
- Ohh!
- She's back early.

02:16.453 --> 02:17.785
Hide.

02:17.821 --> 02:19.254
Hide?

02:19.289 --> 02:21.423
We will tell her eventually,
but not like this.

02:21.458 --> 02:22.690
Why don't you just
lock the door?

02:22.725 --> 02:23.885
'Cause I never lock the door.

02:23.893 --> 02:25.927
- She'll know something's up.
- <i>You still asleep?</i>

02:25.963 --> 02:28.529
Fine.
Where's the closet?

02:28.565 --> 02:30.531
I don't have a closet.
I have an armoire.

02:30.567 --> 02:32.667
Here.
Go out the window.

02:32.702 --> 02:35.269
Are you kidding?
We're on the second floor.

02:35.304 --> 02:36.938
There's a ledge.

02:36.973 --> 02:38.138
Just go out there for a minute,
and I'll get rid of her.

02:38.174 --> 02:39.507
Come on. Go.

02:39.542 --> 02:41.175
- <i>Kyle, honey.</i>
- Kyle. Kyle.

02:41.210 --> 02:43.277
- Kyle.
- Quick, go, go, go!

02:43.312 --> 02:45.212
This is crazy.

02:45.247 --> 02:46.981
Aah!
It's not that high.

02:51.153 --> 02:52.953
Mother. Hey.

02:52.989 --> 02:54.321
Welcome home.

02:54.357 --> 02:55.856
We need to talk about Ben.

02:55.891 --> 02:57.691
Tell me
everything that happened.

02:57.726 --> 02:59.126
Yeah. Absolutely.

02:59.161 --> 03:01.628
But first, tell me...
how was your trip?

03:02.831 --> 03:04.364
How was that?

03:04.399 --> 03:06.399
Fine. Why?

03:07.769 --> 03:09.002
What's wrong?

03:09.037 --> 03:10.670
I got to put some clothes on.

03:10.706 --> 03:12.238
I'll be downstairs in a sec.

03:12.273 --> 03:13.507
Okay. All right.
Okay.

03:17.178 --> 03:19.379
Zoila! You okay?

03:19.414 --> 03:21.680
I'm fine.

03:21.716 --> 03:23.983
I'm so sorry.
I'll call you later.

